#note this is actually a massive error in judgment on my part. If I dump the F, my CEPRS? leave has a 1/3 chance of hitting a triple-triple on column O! Given the importance of spread as a tiebreaker, I should undoubtedly chase that opportunity, even if my intent is highly transparent (after all, I could just play an F at O8 for more points). The bingos on column O are worth a whopping 191 points and up, and even if he blocks, I still often have a bingo to the E on row 15.
